  "title": "Marine Service Engineer | Loyang | Up to $4,500",
  "description": "<h3>About the Role</h3>\n<p>Join a leading marine engineering company to support vessel repair, troubleshooting, and technical service operations. We are seeking a hands-on <strong>Marine Service Engineer</strong> to provide mechanical repair expertise, routine maintenance, and customer technical support for local and regional clients.</p>\n<h3>Responsibilities</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Carry out mechanical repairs onboard vessels and in workshops.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoot and dismantle components to identify mechanical defects.</li>\n  <li>Perform installation, training, and repairs of vessel spare parts and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Realign and reassemble components; test systems for proper operation.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical advice and training to customers on equipment features.</li>\n  <li>Support ship maneuvering systems, main engines, auxiliary engines, hydraulic systems, and coolers.</li>\n  <li>Conduct routine maintenance and ensure compliance with marine safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Undertake ad-hoc assignments such as COP works, cooler works, and hydraulic repairs.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>NTC / Higher NTC in Mechanical or Marine-related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in the Marine Industry preferred.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with marine rules, regulations, and safety standards.</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills; able to work independently and in teams.</li>\n  <li>Willing to work outdoors and perform overtime support when required.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>EA License No.: 23C1703</strong><br>\n <strong>EA Personnel No.: R1762582</strong><br>\n <strong>EA Personnel Name:</strong> Jabez Wong</p>",
